      "title": "How Google's Waymo is Scaling Robotaxis in 2026",
      "link": "https://www.ai-supremacy.com/p/how-googles-waymo-is-scaling-robotaxis-in-2026",
      "published": "2026-06-25",
      "content": "\n\n2026年6月25日。\n\n来自台风侵袭的台湾台中市，向各位道一声早安。我致力于让读者从多个角度全面了解人工智能的演变。这个领域有着令人惊讶的众多面向。\n\n人工智能的发展速度绝对没有你想象的那么快——只需看看智能汽车和自动驾驶汽车就知道了。即使是全球范围内在这一领域做得最好的公司，也需要数十年时间来实现规模化。\n\n谈到物理人工智能，既有前沿探索，也有现实状况。我们作为消费者在物理世界中体验人工智能的一个重要方式将是自动驾驶汽车。\n\n实事求是地说，人工智能和新兴技术（如自动驾驶汽车、机器人、人形机器人、拥有数百万量子比特的量子计算机，甚至更具想象力的太空数据中心）这些更困难的物理应用，要变成现实将极其困难。总体而言，它们需要更长的时间才能到来，速度会更慢，能力也会比你想象的更弱。创新是艰难的，天知道我们已经足够耐心了。（人工智能发展如此之快的说法在经验上并不正确。）我希望我们能以更加务实求真的态度来报道人工智能。\n\n想想看，即使是Waymo到达现在这个位置也花了多长时间。Waymo最初成立于2009年1月。2026年6月11日，Waymo终于在选定城市推出了每月29.99美元的高级订阅服务（称为Premier）。该服务将于今年在旧金山、洛杉矶和凤凰城等选定城市启动。在自动驾驶初创公司方面，我也非常看好Wayve——这家获得英伟达支持的英国初创公司正在开发用于自动驾驶的软件和人工智能模型。无论是否有司机，消费者的偏好在未来几年都可能发生根本性转变。如果价格不是问题，你会选择什么？\n\n自动驾驶汽车和机器人出租车距离大规模普及仍有数年之遥。虽然我们中的一些人已经体验过，但大多数人还没有。物理数据中心和人工智能基础设施的大规模建设正面临大量瓶颈。在现实世界中实现人工智能应用确实极具挑战性。然而，当我们进入2030年代时，将会相当令人振奋。自动驾驶汽车和机器人出租车无疑是这方面最引人入胜的案例研究之一。另一个我越来越着迷的行业——太空技术，也将如此。\n\n今天的文章主要聚焦于Waymo。同时，我也想向大家介绍一些我关注的自动驾驶和出行相关的通讯订阅。\n\n哈里·坎贝尔（Harry Campbell）的《自动驾驶通讯》（Driverless Digest）最近分享了这张图片：\n\n除了Waymo，还有许多其他值得关注的名字。亚马逊的Zoox和Mobileye也在机器人出租车领域取得了进展，并制定了更大的计划。英特尔控股的Mobileye计划于2027年在某个美国主要城市推出首批100辆车的车队，并希望在接下来五年内将车队规模扩大到约17,000辆。\n\n谷歌分拆出来的Waymo是当之无愧的领导者，今年早些时候完成了160亿美元的融资轮，估值超过1260亿美元。Alphabet在Waymo的股份估计很可能远超70%。因此，当我们说谷歌是一家全栈人工智能公司时，我们不仅在谈论垂直整合和应用层，还在谈论最具体可见的东西——比如交通和TPU这些核心技术。这一切都因谷歌在2026年出色的融资表现而得到加强。在自动驾驶和人工智能基础设施领域，Alphabet的未来极其光明。\n\nWaymo将以自己的方式挑战优步，但也面临众多全球竞争对手，如百度阿波罗（Apollo Go）、小马智行、文远知行、特斯拉以及众多其他公司。今年3月，优步宣布了一项重大合作计划，到2031年将投资高达12.5亿美元，部署多达50,000辆完全自动驾驶的Rivian R2机器人出租车，专门在优步平台上运行。玩家和合作模式如此众多，即使是我们这些密切关注这一领域的人也感到眼花缭乱。Waymo将如何挑战优步，这些合作在不同地区又将如何演变？\n\n在驾驶安全和乘客安全方面，Waymo的表现也相当令人瞩目。即使Waymo已扩展到机场和新城市等日益复杂的环境，安全优势仍在不断积累。这对整个自动驾驶行业来说是个好兆头。尽管总会有一些有趣或吓人的事故成为新闻头条，但总体而言，技术仍在不断进步。\n\nWaymo将自己定位为道路上的Anthropic，声称比普通人类司机安全10倍。这确实让人不禁驻足思考。\n\n如果你对自动驾驶新闻感兴趣，我最推荐的订阅之一是。我请他为我们深入分析Waymo——这是今天的专题文章。\n\n深度解析小马智行：商业模式、单位经济、车队数据、财务状况等\n\nWaymo令人震惊的数据发布，优步投资1亿美元建设机器人出租车基础设施\n\nMobileye加入机器人出租车竞赛\n\nWaymo的大师计划\n\n敬请关注这个主题的一些社区通讯订阅：\n\n我不知道未来会怎样，但Waymo很可能就在其中。\n\n现在让我们进入丹尼尔的深度分析。",
      "summary": "<div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" href=\"https://www.ai-supremacy.com/subscribe\" target=\"_blank\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><source type=\"image/webp\" /><img alt=\"Waymo dominates autonomous vehicle registrations as Tesla trails behind |  TechCrunch\" class=\"sizing-large\" height=\"799.21875\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!GntR!,w_2400,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F765fd0d1-0e7c-4e5c-bf27-b8f6f2bb8f7f_1024x682.jpeg\" title=\"Waymo dominates autonomous vehicle registrations as Tesla trails behind |  TechCrunch\" width=\"1200\" /><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg fill=\"none\" height=\"20\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" width=\"20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\" fill=\"none\" height=\"20\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a><figcaption class=\"image-caption\">Waymo. <strong>This stuff is hard.</strong> Watch out for the <a href=\"https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/ckgplyxxl75o\">floods</a> and <a href=\"https://autos.yahoo.com/ev-and-future-tech/articles/waymo-plowed-construction-zone-floored-141000891.html\">construction</a> zones. Click on the title to read on the web! </figcaption></figure></div><p><strong>June 25, 2026. </strong></p><p>Good Morning from typhoon drenched Taichung, Taiwan. I try to give my readers broad exposure to AI&#8217;s evolution from multiple angles. There&#8217;s a surprising number of aspects to this. </p><p><em>AI definitely doesn&#8217;t <strong>move as fast as you think</strong>, just take smart cars and autonomous vehicles. Even the best companies doing this in the world are taking decades to scale.</em> </p><div><hr /></div><ul><li><p>On the topic of Physical AI <a href=\"https://www.ai-supremacy.com/p/rise-of-the-artificial-general-engineer-prometheus\">there are the frontiers</a> and then <strong>there&#8217;s the reality</strong>. An important part of how we as consumers experience AI in the physical reality is going to be <strong>autonomous vehicles</strong> (AVs). </p></li><li><p>Let&#8217;s be real, difficult more physical manifestations of AI and emerging tech like AVs, robotics, humanoids, <a href=\"https://www.thequantumfoundry.com/\">Quantum computers</a> with millions of qubits and even more <a href=\"https://aswathdamodaran.substack.com/p/revisiting-the-spacex-valuation-a\">speculative ideas like datacenters in space</a> are going to be exceedingly difficult to turn into reality. They will on the whole <strong>take more time, be slower to arrive and be less capable</strong> than you think. Innovation is hard, and God knows we&#8217;ve been patient. [The idea that AI is moving so fast isn&#8217;t empirically correct]. I&#8217;d like to see us cover AI with more realism. </p></li><li><p>Think about how long it&#8217;s taken even Waymo to arrive at this point. Waymo was originally founded in January, 2009. On June 11th, 2026 Waymo finally launched a premier <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/06/11/waymo-launches-premier-subscription-tier-for-29point99-a-month.html\">subscription tier for $29.99 a month</a> in select cities (called <a href=\"https://waymo.com/blog/2026/06/waymo-premier/\">Premier</a>). It&#8217;s starting this year in select cities such as San Francisco, Los Angeles and Phoenix. In terms of AV startups, I&#8217;m also really bullish on <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/24/wayve-fundraise-nvidia-microsoft.html\">Wayve</a>, an Nvidia backed UK based startup who are building AV based software and AI models for autonomy. </p><p> </p><h3>What&#8217;s your taxi ride preference? &#128506;&#65039;</h3></li></ul><p>Driver or no-driver, consumer preferences might shift radically in the years ahead. If price wasn&#8217;t a factor what would you use?</p><div class=\"poll-embed\"></div><h2>Physical AI is Hard, Autonomy is Tricky </h2><p>AVs and robotaxis are still years away from scale and while some of us have experienced them, most of us still have not. The build out of physical datacenters and AI Infrastructure at scale is hitting a crazy number of bottlenecks. Manifesting AI in the real world is <strong>just incredibly challenging</strong>. By the time we arrive in the 2030s however it&#8217;s going to be pretty exciting. Autonomous vehicles (AVs) and Robotaxis have to be one of the most fascinating case studies of this. As will another industry I&#8217;m also becoming pretty obsessed with, <a href=\"https://stockquest.substack.com/\">space-technologies</a>. </p><p>Today&#8217;s article is going to be primarily about <a href=\"https://waymo.com/\">Waymo</a>. I also want to introduce you to some of the AV and mobility related Newsletters I follow. </p><p><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/harrygcampbell/\">Harry Campbell</a> of the <a href=\"https://www.thedriverlessdigest.com/\">Driverless Digest Newsletter</a> shared this image recently: </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!4F6O!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc487f585-c2cf-41a0-8b24-613d73150a1c_5712x4284.jpeg\" target=\"_blank\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><source type=\"image/webp\" /><img alt=\"\" class=\"sizing-normal\" height=\"1092\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!4F6O!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc487f585-c2cf-41a0-8b24-613d73150a1c_5712x4284.jpeg\" width=\"1456\" /><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg fill=\"none\" height=\"20\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" width=\"20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\" fill=\"none\" height=\"20\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a><figcaption class=\"image-caption\">The Driverless Digest Newsletter, <a href=\"https://substack.com/@harrycampbell/note/c-281925857?r=cxsa3&amp;utm_source=notes-share-action&amp;utm_medium=web\">Harry Campbell</a>. </figcaption></figure></div><p>Besides Waymo, there are many other interesting names. There&#8217;s the likes of (Amazon&#8217;s) <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2025/06/18/amazon-zoox-robotaxi.html\">Zoox </a>and <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/06/16/self-driving-tech-supplier-mobileye-targets-us-robotaxi-launch-in-2027.html\">Mobileye</a> who are also making headway and bigger plans in the Robotaxi direction. Intel majority owned Mobileye is aiming for and initial 100-vehicle fleet into a major U.S. city in 2027 and hoping to scale the fleet to roughly 17,000 vehicles over the next five years. </p><p>Google spin-off Waymo is however the outright leader, with a $16 Billion <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/02/02/waymo-announced-16-billion-fundraising-round.html\">funding round</a> earlier this year and a valuation of over $126 Billion.  Alphabet&#8217;s stake in Waymo is estimated to be likely well over 70%. So when we say Google is a full-stack AI company - we aren&#8217;t just talking vertical integration and the application layer but the most tangible things like transportation <a href=\"https://blog.google/innovation-and-ai/infrastructure-and-cloud/google-cloud/eighth-generation-tpu-agentic-era/\">and TPUs</a>, the nuts and bolts. All of this is compounded by how well Google has <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/06/01/alphabet-to-raise-80-billion-from-stock-sales-to-fund-ai-buildout.html\">raised capital</a> in 2026. Autonomy and AI infrastructure are just two areas where Alphabet&#8217;s future is <a href=\"https://blog.google/innovation-and-ai/infrastructure-and-cloud/google-cloud/blackstone-tpu-cloud/\">exceedingly bright</a>.  </p><p>Waymo will be taking on Uber in its own way but have several global rivals such as <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2025/11/20/global-robotaxi-race-heats-up-between-us-and-chinese-rivals.html\">Baidu Apollo</a> (Apollo Go), Pony.AI, WeRide, <a href=\"https://www.tesla.com/robotaxi\">Tesla</a> and a host of others. In March, Uber <a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2026/03/19/uber-rivian-robotaxi.html\">announced a massive partnership</a> to invest up to $1.25 billion through 2031 to deploy up to 50,000 fully autonomous <strong>Rivian R2 robotaxis</strong> exclusively on the Uber platform. There are so many players and so many partnerships, it&#8217;s a bit confusing even for us who watch the space. How will Waymo challenge Uber and how will all of these partnerships pan out in different regions of the world? </p><p>Waymo&#8217;s track record is also fairly stunning when it comes to the driver and passenger saftey aspect: Even as Waymo has scaled into increasingly complex environments like airports and new cities, the safety benefits kept compounding. It&#8217;s a good sign for the AV industry. While there&#8217;s always the funny or scary story of some headline mishap, for the most part the tech is improving. </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!zFPn!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F117a7027-008e-4e8d-9b14-f55890b699eb_1080x1350.png\" target=\"_blank\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><source type=\"image/webp\" /><img alt=\"Image\" class=\"sizing-normal\" height=\"523.75\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!zFPn!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F117a7027-008e-4e8d-9b14-f55890b699eb_1080x1350.png\" title=\"Image\" width=\"419\" /><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg fill=\"none\" height=\"20\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" width=\"20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\" fill=\"none\" height=\"20\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a><figcaption class=\"image-caption\">Waymo&#8217;s lifetime miles and saftey record is getting impressive. </figcaption></figure></div><p>Waymo is marketing itself a bit like <a href=\"https://waymo.com/safety/\">the Anthropic of the road</a>, and as <strong>being 10x safer than an average human driver</strong>. It certainly makes you <a href=\"https://www.thedriverlessdigest.com/p/waymo-master-plan\">pause and wonder</a>. </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2\" href=\"https://waymo.com/safety/\" target=\"_blank\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><source type=\"image/webp\" /><img alt=\"\" class=\"sizing-normal\" height=\"96.65587044534414\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!Z1XN!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd1066cfa-6afe-4b04-80e7-742603b8daba_494x173.png\" width=\"276\" /><div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>In case you are interested in following autonomous vehicle news one of my favorites is <span class=\"mention-wrap\"></span>. I asked him to do a deep dive for us on Waymo, todays&#8217; piece. </p><h3>The AV Market Strategist </h3><div class=\"embedded-publication-wrap\"><div class=\"embedded-publication show-subscribe\"><a class=\"embedded-publication-link-part\" href=\"https://avmarketstrategist.substack.com?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_campaign=publication_embed&amp;utm_medium=web\"><img class=\"embedded-publication-logo\" height=\"56\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!8eoy!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb5d5b815-741d-428f-b401-d4e2d9fd9621_1000x1000.png\" width=\"56\" /><span class=\"embedded-publication-name\">The AV Market Strategist</span><div class=\"embedded-publication-hero-text\">The AV Market Strategist breaks down strategic developments, market dynamics, and competitive moves in the autonomous vehicle industry to reveal where the market is truly heading.</div><div class=\"embedded-publication-author-name\">By Daniel Abreu Marques</div></a><form action=\"https://avmarketstrategist.substack.com/subscribe?\" class=\"embedded-publication-subscribe\" method=\"GET\"><input name=\"source\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"publication-embed\" /><input name=\"autoSubmit\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"true\" /><input class=\"email-input\" name=\"email\" type=\"email\" /><input class=\"button primary\" type=\"submit\" value=\"Subscribe\" /></form></div></div><ul><li><p><strong>Deep Dive Pony.ai</strong>: <a href=\"https://avmarketstrategist.substack.com/p/deep-dive-ponyai-business-model-unit\">Business Model, Unit Economics, Fleet Data, Financials and More</a></p></li><li><p><strong>WeRide Hits Madrid, </strong><a href=\"https://avmarketstrategist.substack.com/p/deep-dive-ponyai-business-model-unit\">Tesla&#8217;s Map Grows but Its Fleet Doesn&#8217;t, NVIDIA Wants to Be the Robotaxi Standard</a></p></li><li><p><strong>Waymo&#8217;s Shocking Data Release, </strong><a href=\"https://avmarketstrategist.substack.com/p/waymos-shocking-data-release-uber\">Uber Invest $100M in Robotaxi Infrastructure</a></p></li><li><p><strong>Mobileye </strong><a href=\"https://www.thedriverlessdigest.com/p/mobileye-joins-the-robotaxi-race\">Joins the Robotaxi Race</a></p></li><li><p><strong>Waymo&#8217;s </strong><a href=\"https://www.thedriverlessdigest.com/p/waymo-master-plan\">Master Plan</a></p></li></ul><h3>So what does a Waymo look like from the inside?</h3><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!8Dvx!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6739c752-289e-4ffb-a169-348efdf4a4b2_5712x4284.jpeg\" target=\"_blank\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><source type=\"image/webp\" /><img alt=\"\" class=\"sizing-normal\" height=\"1092\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!8Dvx!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6739c752-289e-4ffb-a169-348efdf4a4b2_5712x4284.jpeg\" width=\"1456\" /><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg fill=\"none\" height=\"20\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" width=\"20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\" fill=\"none\" height=\"20\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a><figcaption class=\"image-caption\">The Driverless Digest - <a href=\"https://substack.com/@harrycampbell/note/c-281925857?r=cxsa3\">Harry Campbell. </a></figcaption></figure></div><h3>Autonomous AV and Neo Mobility Newsletters of Note &#9991;</h3><p>Check out some of the community Newsletters for this topic: </p><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://www.thedriverlessdigest.com/\">The Driverless Digest</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://selfdrivinginsights.substack.com/\">Self Driving Insights</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://www.ottomate.news/\">Ottomate</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://www.readmovements.com/\">Movements</a> </p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://www.thecurbivore.com/\">The Curbivore</a></p></li></ul><p>I don&#8217;t know what the future holds but there&#8217;s <strong>probably going to be a Waymo in it</strong>. </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!EZ3A!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff7a08f65-8d3e-4eb0-97e6-9dbe1250b0ca_1055x585.png\" target=\"_blank\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><source type=\"image/webp\" /><img alt=\"\" class=\"sizing-normal\" height=\"585\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!EZ3A!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Ff7a08f65-8d3e-4eb0-97e6-9dbe1250b0ca_1055x585.png\" width=\"1055\" /><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg fill=\"none\" height=\"20\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" width=\"20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\" fill=\"none\" height=\"20\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a><figcaption class=\"image-caption\">Waymo, Twitter. </figcaption></figure></div><p>Let&#8217;s get on to our deep dive now by Daniel. </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!qB_6!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb944bde2-d243-4e93-92a4-43ee872a32bf_1115x508.png\" target=\"_blank\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><source type=\"image/webp\" /><img alt=\"\" class=\"sizing-normal\" height=\"508\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!qB_6!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb944bde2-d243-4e93-92a4-43ee872a32bf_1115x508.png\" width=\"1115\" /><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg fill=\"none\" height=\"20\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" width=\"20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\" fill=\"none\" height=\"20\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" width=\"20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a><figcaption class=\"image-caption\">It took Waymo a lot of miles to realize it&#8217;s a bad idea to<a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2026/06/18/waymo-recalls-nearly-4000-robotaxis-to-stop-them-driving-into-highway-construction-zones/\"> drive into construction zones. </a></figcaption></figure></div><h1><span style=\"color: rgb(106, 168, 79);\">Waymo: The Company That Solved Self-Driving and Now Has to Scale It</span></h1>\n      <p>\n          <a href=\"https://www.ai-supremacy.com/p/how-googles-waymo-is-scaling-robotaxis-in-2026\">\n              Read more\n          </a>\n      </p>",
